threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: Statically linked x86 IoT botnet (Mirai/Gafgyt variant). The binary contains clear indicators of automated exploitation targeting the Huawei HG532 router vulnerability (CVE-2017-17215). Function sub_804b9d0 constructs a SOAP envelope targeting '/ctrlt/DeviceUpgrade_1' with a shell injection payload in 'NewStatusURL' $(/bin/busybox wget...). It utilizes hardcoded credentials ('dslf-config' / 'HuaweiHomeGateway') for authentication. Additional malicious behaviors include a process killer (sub_804c5c0) that scans '/proc/net/tcp' to terminate competing services, watchdog disabling via '/dev/watchdog' to prevent device reboots, and a custom network scanning/C2 module (sub_804d8f0).
